1157
01:38:48,000 --> 01:38:56,000
It seems like a life that accepts and responsibility for the norms we're in

1158
01:38:56,000 --> 01:39:00,000
has to constantly be sort of questioning yourself

1159
01:39:00,000 --> 01:39:05,000
and questioning, like listening to the world fully and richly

1160
01:39:05,000 --> 01:39:13,000
without being weighed down by any one sort of realization.

1161
01:39:13,000 --> 01:39:16,000
You just always constantly have to be thinking about the world.

1162
01:39:16,000 --> 01:39:17,000
Am I wrong?

1163
01:39:17,000 --> 01:39:19,000
Am I wrong in seeing the world this way?

1164
01:39:19,000 --> 01:39:21,000
I mean, the very last thing you said,

1165
01:39:21,000 --> 01:39:23,000
you've constantly got to be thinking about the world.

1166
01:39:23,000 --> 01:39:25,000
You've constantly got to be listening.

1167
01:39:25,000 --> 01:39:27,000
You've constantly got to be attending.

1168
01:39:27,000 --> 01:39:28,000
And it's not simple.

1169
01:39:28,000 --> 01:39:30,000
All that sounds exactly right to me.

1170
01:39:30,000 --> 01:39:35,000
And the phrase that rings through my head is another one from the Brothers Karamazov.

1171
01:39:35,000 --> 01:39:39,000
Dimitri, this passionate, sort of sometimes violent brother

1172
01:39:39,000 --> 01:39:45,000
who is also sort of deeply cares.

1173
01:39:45,000 --> 01:39:49,000
Because he's passionate, he's sort of got care through and through,

1174
01:39:49,000 --> 01:39:51,000
but it's breaking him apart.

1175
01:39:51,000 --> 01:39:57,000
He says at one point, God and the devil are fighting in the battlefield

1176
01:39:57,000 --> 01:39:59,000
is the heart of man.

1177
01:39:59,000 --> 01:40:02,000
And I just think, yeah, it's not simple.

